There's lots to do.

131
00:11:36,760 --> 00:11:40,120
Listen, Carl, I need you to sell my truck.

132
00:11:40,280 --> 00:11:41,840
Whatever you can get for it.

133
00:11:41,920 --> 00:11:45,160
I'm just a little short of cash right now.

134
00:11:52,600 --> 00:11:53,960
I'm still here.

135
00:11:54,840 --> 00:11:56,400
Listen, Carl,
there's something else I need...

136
00:11:56,480 --> 00:11:59,440
...and Professor Wells
doesn't have to know about it.

137
00:12:49,640 --> 00:12:52,600
Hey, Linda. How you doing?

138
00:12:55,520 --> 00:12:57,680
You want to hear something funny?

139
00:12:57,840 --> 00:13:00,920
I saw this on the news before I came out.

140
00:13:01,080 --> 00:13:03,440
Fainting goats. I'm not making this up.

141
00:13:03,600 --> 00:13:04,920
There's this breed of goats.

142
00:13:05,000 --> 00:13:07,680
I don't know why, but...

143
00:13:07,840 --> 00:13:10,000
...they faint at the slightest thing.

144
00:13:10,080 --> 00:13:14,040
lf they hear a loud noise
or a gun goes off...

145
00:13:14,680 --> 00:13:18,920
...they black out, fall right over,
one after the other.

146
00:13:24,320 --> 00:13:26,720
I thought you'd like that.

147
00:14:42,160 --> 00:14:43,840
Get off.

148
00:15:02,960 --> 00:15:05,200
I don't even have a chart for that.

149
00:15:09,400 --> 00:15:10,600
Get over here.

150
00:15:11,840 --> 00:15:12,880
Gotcha!

151
00:16:22,480 --> 00:16:24,200
Get away from here!

152
00:16:29,000 --> 00:16:31,720
