180
00:19:43,600 --> 00:19:45,360
Like listening bugging?

181
00:19:45,440 --> 00:19:47,040
Bugging who?

182
00:19:49,360 --> 00:19:51,000
Take a wild guess.

183
00:19:52,480 --> 00:19:54,520
Why would anyone want to do that?

184
00:19:54,600 --> 00:19:56,120
'Cause I want to hear
What goes on in there.

185
00:19:56,200 --> 00:19:58,240
Don't you want to hear
What goes on in there?

186
00:19:58,320 --> 00:19:59,240
No, I do not.

187
00:19:59,320 --> 00:20:00,320
Why not?

188
00:20:00,800 --> 00:20:03,800
'Cause that would be
an invasion of her privacy.

189
00:20:03,960 --> 00:20:05,840
Excuse me, Mr. Video.

190
00:20:06,000 --> 00:20:07,360
That's not a video.

191
00:20:07,440 --> 00:20:08,960
It's a camera obscura.

192
00:20:09,040 --> 00:20:10,320
It's pure light.

193
00:20:10,480 --> 00:20:11,880
I'm not spying.

194
00:20:12,040 --> 00:20:13,840
I just want to be with her.

195
00:20:14,320 --> 00:20:16,080
That's completely different.

196
00:20:16,160 --> 00:20:17,560
I know how you feel.

197
00:20:17,640 --> 00:20:19,960
You want him back so badly
that you can't stand it.

198
00:20:20,040 --> 00:20:21,800
It's like your guts
are twisting around inside.

199
00:20:21,880 --> 00:20:23,680
But bugging their apartment....

200
00:20:23,760 --> 00:20:24,680
What?

201
00:20:25,880 --> 00:20:28,600
I don't want him back.
I want him vaporized.

202
00:20:29,680 --> 00:20:30,840
Extinguished!

203
00:20:31,400 --> 00:20:32,360
When I'm done with him...

204
00:20:32,440 --> 00:20:35,200
...he'll be a twitchy little stain on the floor.

205
00:20:39,960 --> 00:20:41,120
ls that what you're doing?

206
00:20:41,200 --> 00:20:43,720
You're waiting
for her to leave him for you?

207
00:20:44,080 --> 00:20:44,840
Absolutely.

208
00:20:44,920 --> 00:20:46,240
Have you seen him?

209
00:20:46,320 --> 00:20:48,920
He is irrelevant.
Linda and I are soul mates.

210
00:20:49,080 --> 00:20:50,880
This is just a passing phase.

211
00:20:50,960 --> 00:20:53,720
They're going to break up tonight.
I know it.

212
00:20:53,880 --> 00:20:55,080
I'm listening.

213
00:20:55,160 --> 00:20:56,520
I'm an astronomer.

214
00:20:57,400 --> 00:20:59,520
It's my job to find patterns in things...

215
00:20:59,600 --> 00:21:02,040
...that seem completely random.

216
00:21:02,200 --> 00:21:04,720
I found a pattern.

217
00:21:04,880 --> 00:21:06,640
It's all in the data.

218
00:21:07,400 --> 00:21:08,760
The data.

219
00:21:09,200 --> 00:21:10,600
This data.

220
00:21:11,080 --> 00:21:12,880
"Mutual feeding activity."

221
00:21:13,040 --> 00:21:15,120
It's the number of times
that Linda and what's-his-name...

222
00:21:15,200 --> 00:21:16,200
...feed each other.

223
00:21:16,280 --> 00:21:16,920
You're counting.

224
00:21:17,000 --> 00:21:18,760
Not just that. Everything.

225
00:21:19,120 --> 00:21:21,720
Kisses, hugs, smiles, fights.

226
00:21:21,880 --> 00:21:22,920
They fight?

227
00:21:23,000 --> 00:21:24,080
Not yet.

228
00:21:24,240 --> 00:21:26,280
Long looks, whispering, shouting.

229
00:21:26,360 --> 00:21:27,400
They shout?

230
00:21:27,480 --> 00:21:29,160
You're missing the point.

231
00:21:29,240 --> 00:21:31,160
Tonight there's going to be a fight.

232
00:21:31,240 --> 00:21:32,760
They are going to break up...

233
00:21:32,840 --> 00:21:34,960
...and I'm going to be right here for her.

234
00:21:35,040 --> 00:21:37,040
Tonight this will all be over...

235
00:21:37,120 --> 00:21:39,920
...so you might as well start packing
your bags.

236
00:21:40,680 --> 00:21:44,760
That is the most pathetic thing
I've ever heard.

237
00:21:45,520 --> 00:21:46,760
I don't mean that trivially.

238
00:21:46,840 --> 00:21:48,680
I'm a photographer.
I've seen a lot of things.

239
00:21:48,760 --> 00:21:51,720
I once took pictures
of a man who ate his own legs...

240
00:21:51,920 --> 00:21:53,480
...and you would be the black sheep
of that family.

241
00:21:53,560 --> 00:21:56,480
What's your evil plan?
Squirt him with squirt guns?

242
00:21:56,560 --> 00:21:58,120
Throw rotten strawberries at him?

243
00:21:58,200 --> 00:21:59,560
You looked in my satchel?

244
00:21:59,640 --> 00:22:01,000
Yeah. Call a cop.

245
00:22:02,040 --> 00:22:04,720
You are a strange, tragic little man.

246
00:22:04,800 --> 00:22:07,240
Say what you want.
Linda and I are in love.

247
00:22:07,400 --> 00:22:08,920
Except for her boning my boyfriend...

248
00:22:09,000 --> 00:22:10,200
...you guys are the perfect couple.

249
00:22:10,280 --> 00:22:12,760
Listen, Catwoman, at the end of the day...

250
00:22:12,920 --> 00:22:15,560
...she is coming back to me,
and we're going to be happy.

251
00:22:15,640 --> 00:22:16,680
And where are you going to be?

252
00:22:16,760 --> 00:22:19,960
All alone somewhere,
hatching some little revenge scheme.

253
00:22:23,120 --> 00:22:24,760
Let me tell you something, Sam.

254
00:22:24,840 --> 00:22:27,440
Listen very carefully. Are you listening?

255
00:22:28,000 --> 00:22:29,880
The only way that girl
is coming back to you...

256
00:22:29,960 --> 00:22:31,720
...is if a blast of semen catapults her...

257
00:22:31,800 --> 00:22:34,320
...across the street
and through the window.

258
00:22:36,960 --> 00:22:38,360
I want you out.

259
00:22:39,120 --> 00:22:40,280
Not going to happen.

260
00:22:40,360 --> 00:22:41,560
I was here first.

261
00:22:41,640 --> 00:22:44,840
Put me down for half the rent
and get out of my face.

262
00:22:49,280 --> 00:22:51,240
I wouldn't do that if I were you.

263
00:22:51,320 --> 00:22:52,280
Why not?

264
00:22:52,360 --> 00:22:53,720
You paid for it.

265
00:22:57,800 --> 00:22:59,240
You stole my money.

266
00:22:59,400 --> 00:23:01,200
You took everything I had to buy this crap?

267
00:23:01,280 --> 00:23:03,040
That was everything you had?

268
00:23:03,120 --> 00:23:05,920
What the hell is that for, anyway?

269
00:23:07,080 --> 00:23:09,600
It's pretty, Sam.

270
00:23:22,360 --> 00:23:23,800
There we go.

