01:24:54,000 --> 01:24:55,880
Maggie was my angel.

1330
01:24:59,440 --> 01:25:02,600
She brought me here, in America.

1331
01:25:03,120 --> 01:25:05,120
I was nothing before I met her.

1332
01:25:05,320 --> 01:25:08,880
Just a waiter in a little café in Paris.

1333
01:25:11,800 --> 01:25:14,320
Yeah. I used her.

1334
01:25:15,480 --> 01:25:17,320
I used her terribly.

1335
01:25:18,400 --> 01:25:20,960
But I didn't think it mattered...

1336
01:25:22,120 --> 01:25:23,720
...because I was...

1337
01:25:23,880 --> 01:25:27,240
...sure that I would grow to love her.

1338
01:25:30,080 --> 01:25:32,960
I thought if I could just love her, then...

1339
01:25:35,000 --> 01:25:37,080
...it would be all right.

1340
01:25:38,760 --> 01:25:40,680
The shame would go away.

1341
01:25:42,320 --> 01:25:44,680
You can't choose who you love, Mike...

1342
01:25:44,840 --> 01:25:46,920
...or whoever the hell you are...

1343
01:25:47,600 --> 01:25:49,280
...and I love Linda.

1344
01:25:49,440 --> 01:25:51,160
I love Linda.

1345
01:25:57,120 --> 01:25:58,880
More than anything!

1346
01:26:08,920 --> 01:26:11,800
Who the hell do you think
you are to judge?

1347
01:26:12,080 --> 01:26:14,520
Who the hell do you think you are?

1348
01:26:16,400 --> 01:26:18,080
I'm nobody, Anton.

1349
01:26:21,440 --> 01:26:22,560
I'm nobody.

1350
01:26:25,440 --> 01:26:27,120
Nobody to nobody.

1351
01:27:02,000 --> 01:27:04,040
Linda, we need to talk.

1352
01:27:13,640 --> 01:27:15,320
Hello? Yes, please.

1353
01:27:16,120 --> 01:27:19,760
I need to be scratched on my face,
my chest, and my back.

1354
01:27:20,400 --> 01:27:22,160
Please. Hello?

1355
01:27:24,720 --> 01:27:27,600
lt is an emergency call. I swear.

1356
01:27:28,200 --> 01:27:30,120
Hello, mister?

1357
01:28:13,320 --> 01:28:14,920
Say we're even.

1358
01:28:15,000 --> 01:28:16,760
-What?
-Just say it.

1359
01:28:19,600 --> 01:28:21,400
Yes, we are even.

1360
01:28:21,560 --> 01:28:22,680
Good.

1361
01:28:26,920 --> 01:28:28,440
So how ya been?

1362
01:29:07,000 --> 01:29:09,240
Here! I'm here, Linda!

1363
01:29:10,000 --> 01:29:12,080
Oh, baby! Look at you!

1364
01:29:13,440 --> 01:29:14,720
Oh, God!

1365
01:29:15,280 --> 01:29:17,400
Oh, honey!

1366
01:29:18,160 --> 01:29:19,600
I love you.

1367
01:29:20,760 --> 01:29:22,880
You're everything to me.

1368
01:30:26,880 --> 01:30:28,600
Bad dog! Go away!

1369
01:31:33,440 --> 01:31:36,200
So I saw this episode of Lassie today...

1370
01:31:37,480 --> 01:31:41,120
...and Lassie was accused
of a crime she didn't commit...

1371
01:31:42,560 --> 01:31:45,840
...and the ranger was coming
to put her to sleep.

1372
01:31:47,800 --> 01:31:50,240
How's Lassie going to get out of this one?

1373
01:31:50,800 --> 01:31:54,400
Well, the little boy found out
that the ranger was coming...

1374
01:31:54,680 --> 01:31:56,800
...and he told Lassie that...

1375
01:31:57,560 --> 01:32:00,000
...that she had to go away, far away.

1376
01:32:00,080 --> 01:32:01,400
For her own good.

1377
01:32:01,480 --> 01:32:03,920
But Lassie wouldn't leave.

1378
01:32:04,680 --> 01:32:07,440
See, Lassie just couldn't leave the boy.

1379
01:32:09,600 --> 01:32:11,160
What did he do?

1380
01:32:12,320 --> 01:32:14,640
He told her that he never liked her.

1381
01:32:14,720 --> 01:32:16,960
He said, "l hate you.

1382
01:32:17,520 --> 01:32:19,960
"l hate you, Lassie. You're a bad dog.

1383
01:32:20,520 --> 01:32:22,400
"l hope I never see you again."

1384
01:32:22,480 --> 01:32:24,440
That must have made Lassie sad.

1385
01:32:24,720 --> 01:32:25,560
Yes, it did.

1386
01:32:25,640 --> 01:32:28,080
Lassie trotted off...

1387
01:32:28,240 --> 01:32:29,600
...very sadly.

1388
01:32:32,000 --> 01:32:33,920
But you know what happened?

1389
01:32:35,880 --> 01:32:37,960
Lassie came home, Maggie.

1390
01:32:38,240 --> 01:32:40,920
Did the little boy make it with Lassie?

1391
01:32:44,080 --> 01:32:45,440
Yes, he did.

1392
01:33:07,320 --> 01:33:11,000


1393
01:36:39,520 --> 01:36:40,920
You can hear them?

1394
01:36:41,520 --> 01:36:42,880
Are they talking?

1395
01:36:43,240 --> 01:36:45,040
-What about?
-You wouldn't be interested.

1396
01:36:45,120 --> 01:36:47,280
I just want to hear her sweet voice.

1397
01:36:49,400 --> 01:36:51,320
Oh, my God. He's killing her.

1398
01:36:51,840 --> 01:36:53,680
He's killing her, all right.

1399
01:36:54,200 --> 01:36:56,280
That girl of yours is a carnival ride.

1400
01:36:56,360 --> 01:36:58,120
This is worse than I'd imagined.

